The Federal Government of Nigeria has expressed its readiness to cooperate with sister countries and development bodies to advance Africa’s prosperity through the safe and sustainable use of the continent’s vast sea and ocean resources. The Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, made this known in his speech at the first Sustainable Blue Economy Conference, which held in Nairobi. Amaechi, who was represented by the Director-General of the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA) and Chairman of the Association of African Maritime Administrations (AAMA), Dr. Dakuku Peterside, conveyed Nigeria’s statement of commitment to the blue economy initiative and said its growth was the most viable option for Africa’s development in the wake of declining mineral and commodity prices.  NIMASA to send anti-piracy bill to National Assembly soon - DG ‘How Buhari is battling poverty’ Nigeria, Ghana sign MoU on maritime operations